status: canonical
layer: runtime
domain: work
scope: work.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines core runtime handling for work.

## runtime_scope
Runtime covers work visibility,
assignment state,
executor state,
progress state,
review state,
and bounded failure rendering.

## current_view_state
Runtime-visible work state must distinguish:
- proposed work
- assigned work
- active work
- blocked work
- review work
- closed work
- historical work

## validation_rules
- work identity must resolve
- assigning authority must resolve
- executor scope must resolve
- task scope must be valid
- policy/boundary scope must be valid

## failure_modes
- invalid assignment authority
- invalid executor scope
- invalid task scope
- invalid closure path
- safe runtime fallback

## observability
Runtime must expose enough signals
to distinguish assignment,
execution,
review,
closure,
and failure state.

## review_checklist
- work states are explicit
- role-aware visibility is explicit
- validation gating is explicit
- failure rendering is explicit
